title: $5.2 billion in cargo stuck off West Coast ports in truck and container bottleneck
description: The West Coast port labor union battle has held up over $5 billion in ocean cargo and led to a pileup up trucks, railroads and containers.

title: Crypto tokens plunged this week after Gensler stepped up SEC's industrywide crackdown
description: Several of the most valuable cryptocurrencies dropped more than 15% this week after the SEC filed lawsuits against Coinbase and Binance.

title: Tesla on track to match its longest winning streak on heels of GM charging deal
description: The streak follows Tesla's announcement Thursday that General Motors would join Ford in using its electric vehicle charging network to charge their cars.

title: Stocks making the biggest moves midday: Sonoma Pharmaceuticals, Braze, Adobe and more
description: These are the stocks posting the largest moves in midday trading.

title: JPMorgan bond chief Bob Michele sees worrying echoes of 2008 in market calm
description: Economic crosscurrents have divided the investing world into roughly two camps: Those who see a soft landing, and those who envision something far worse.

title: Trump lawyers quit classified documents case
description: Trump said lawyers Jim Trusty and John Rowley will be replaced by Todd Blanche, who represents him in his porn star payoff criminal case in New York.

title: Epstein accuser seeks new testimony from JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon
description: JPMorgan Chase is being sued by a victim of Jeffrey Epstein allegedly facilitating his sex trafficking of young women. CEO Jamie Dimon denies any wrongdoing.

title: GE nears deal with India's Hindustan Aeronautics to co-manufacture fighter jet engines
description: The deal is expected to be signed either before or during a visit by Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi to Washington, D.C., later this month.

title: Prince Harry took to the witness stand in UK court this week: Here’s what’s going on
description: Prince Harry became the first high-ranking British royal to take to the witness stand in more than 130 years this week.

title: HSBC pulls some UK mortgage deals as fears of rising rates hits home buyers once more
description: Analysts expect mortgage rates to soar and housing prices to plummet in the U.K., as the effect of higher interest rates ripples through the British housing market.

title: 'Fight has only just begun': Climate activist Greta Thunberg holds her final school strike
description: Greta Thunberg on Friday took part in her last school strike, signing off after 251 weeks of demonstrations with a warning that "the fight has only just begun."

title: Nearly half of people under 40 are hoping to retire before they're 60 years old, according to the World Economic Forum
description: This is a "significant disconnect" between people's retirement aims, and what is likely to happen in reality, according to the World Economic Forum.

title: Ukraine's dam disaster is 'unlikely' to derail its plans for a counteroffensive against Russia
description: The Nova Kakhovka dam breach comes amid months of buildup to Ukraine's counteroffensive, a phase of the war that many see as potentially pivotal.

title: Turkey's Erdogan appoints a former Goldman executive as its new central bank chief
description: Turkey's President Recep Tayyip Erdogan has appointed U.S. finance executive Hafize Gaye Erkan as the country's new central bank governor.

title: UBS and the Swiss government sign loss protection agreement over Credit Suisse takeover
description: UBS and the Swiss government announced Friday that they had signed a loss protection agreement which will come into effect once the takeover of Credit Suisse is completed.

title: Tech leaders are calling for an A.I. pause because they have no product ready, Palantir CEO says
description: Palantir CEO Alex Karp said that to pause research and study A.I. will only give the lead to adversaries.

title: China can't rely on Southeast Asian exports to offset a U.S. slowdown
description: China's exports to the U.S. and Southeast Asian countries fell sharply in May.

title: Banks are cutting off Binance's access to U.S. banking system, exchange says
description: Binance's banking partners will "pause" Binance.US' access to US dollar deposits as soon as next week, after the SEC filed charges against the exchange.

title: Biden and UK's Sunak sign 'Atlantic Declaration,' pledging agreements on A.I. and critical minerals
description: Rishi Sunak, coming to the end of his U.S. trip this week, lauded the deal as a "new economic partnership for a new age."

title: China's producer prices slump 4.6% in May, worse than expected
India predicted to outshine China as Asia remains a bright spot for global growth
description: In its latest global economic outlook report, the OECD predicted India, China and Indonesia would top gross domestic product projections for 2023 and 2024.

title: Train review: What it’s like to ride the Venice Simplon-Orient-Express
description: Paying $2,000 for a hotel room is pricey, but an overnight ride on the historic Venice Simplon-Orient-Express trains costs about as much —  per square meter.

title: Trump indicted on seven criminal counts in classified documents case
description: Former President Donald Trump said in a Truth Social post that he had been indicted and summoned to appear at federal court in Miami on Tuesday.
